# UI & Theme

- Always use theme tokens: `@/theme/colors`, `@/theme/spacing`, `@/theme/admin`, `@prime/ui` typography
- `StyleSheet.create` only. No inline style objects, no NativeWind `className`
  strings duplicating what a token already covers.
- If a needed color/spacing value doesn't exist in the current token set:
  STOP and ask whether to add it to the theme file, rather than hardcoding
  a one-off value inline. Hardcoded hex values are a rules violation, not
  a style preference.
- Admin surfaces use the admin accent; Customer/Officer share the primary
  accent. Never mix accent sets within a single screen.
- Every list, sheet, modal, and form must use the shared components in
  `@prime/ui` where one exists — check there before building a new primitive.
- Required states on every data-driven screen: loading (skeleton, not
  spinner-only), error (with retry action), empty (with explanation +
  next action, not just "No data").
- Forms: React Hook Form + Zod only. Validation errors render inline,
  not via Alert/toast, unless the existing pattern in the codebase does
  otherwise — check an existing form first.

## Role-specific accents

**Admin** (`apps/unified-app/src/screens/admin/`)

- Canvas: `adminColors.canvasBg`
- Cards: `adminColors.cardBg`
- Primary actions / active states: `adminColors.primary`
- Reuse `@/components/admin`: `FormField`, `SelectField`, `DateField`, `SectionCard`, `FilterChips`, `StatusBadge`, `KPICard`

**Customer / Officer**

- Accent: `colors.primaryNavy`
- Canvas: `colors.background`
- Reuse `@/components/common` and `@prime/ui` (`Screen`, `Button`, `EmptyState`)

## Lists, sheets & modals

- Lists: `FlatList` with stable `keyExtractor` and memoized `renderItem`
- Sheets: surface `colors.surfaceWhite`, top corners `radius.lg`, backdrop `colors.overlay`
- Sheet header: Cancel / title / Done row with `colors.borderDefault` divider

## Form field styling

- Labels: 12px, weight 600, `colors.textSecondary`, uppercase
- Inputs: 1px `colors.borderDefault` border, `radius.sm`, `spacing.sm` padding, `colors.surfaceWhite` background
- Error state: `colors.errorRed` border and helper text
